commit.title: [ci] [flambda] Raise stack limit for OCaml compiler.
commit.message:
[ci] [flambda] Raise stack limit for OCaml compiler.

As of today flambda is pretty stack-hungry for some development so we
increase the stack limit for the .ci-template.

We do this in the general case as it doesn't hurt and avoids
duplication, we could introduce an env variable but IMHO not worth it.

This fixes fiat-crypto failing when compiling extracted code.
